column2: WDNR's 1978 Surface Water Resources of Washburn County states secchi reading of 10'- and states measurements were taken in July of 1968 (wch)
DNR Lake map drawn August 1976 states water level is 84.00 relative to spike in power pole = 100.00 (wch)

Bill Hoveland and John Haack set new temporary benchmarks (nails in trees) relative to original spike in pole.  Holes were drilled in ice to measure water level at  86.10 feet relative to original 100 Bill Hoveland and John Haack set new temporary benchmarks (nails in trees) relative to original spike in pole.  Holes were drilled in ice to measure water level at  86.10 feet relative to original 100 (wch)
DNR staff set concrete monument at public access.  Monument level is 90.40 relative to spike in post (100).  Water level (wch)
Mostly cloudy NE wind- mild and intermittent. Mild algae bloom resident loon observed.
Mostly sunny mild breeze out of NE. Increased algae bloom.
SW wind. Slightly reduced algae bloom.  Saw blue herons and frogs.
Moderate easterly wind. Sunny + clear. Pair of loons. 1 canada goose. 1 blue heron. 1 frog. Pair small ducks.
Stiff SE wind. Sunny + clear. Pair loons + blue heron. Frog + sandpiper.
Moderate south wind. Sunny + partly cloudy. 1 loon- pair of mallards- 1 blue heron. Slight algae bloom.
Brisk south wind. 1 pair loons. Partly cloudy. No visible algae bloom.
Sunny. Mild SE breeze. No visible algae bloom.  Data sent to "Great American Secchi Dip-in" as requested/offered.
Mostly sunny. North wind. Algae globules.
Partly cloudy. Water has green algae tint. 1 bald eagle.
Medium to heavy algae bloom. SW wind. Mostly cloudy.
Mostly cloudy. Westerly wind. Medium to heavy algae bloom.
Partly cloudy. Southerly wind. Medium to heavy algae
South wind. Clear + sunny. **Note: lake is low relative to the past four years of my causal observation.  Lake lowered this year between 4/25 - 7/7.  Then appeared to stabilize.
Sunny and cloudless. N breeze. 2 loons- 1 mallard.
Sunny and cloudless.  Light N breeze.  1 loon- 2 mallards.
Sunny and cloudless.  Gusty NE breeze. Errant suburban dog on shoreline.

Mostly sunny. Stiff E wind. Water extremely clear. 2 wood ducks. Water is as low as it has been in 4 years.  The deepest spot (Deep Hole) I've registered this year is 30 feet.  (So with a disc reading of 19'- I was 11 feet off the bottom of the lakebed.).
Overcast and cloudy. SE wind. Reading following heavy sustained rain. Pair of loons. Fireworks debris in water.
Sunny- S wind. High cirrus clouds. Pair of nesting loons. water very clear.
Satellite passover date. Secchi test followed 2 weeks of clouds and rain. Sunny- calm.  Slight algae bloom.
Following 3 days of heavy sustained rain. Great North American Secchi Dip-in. Sunny- NW wind. No algae bloom.
Satellite pass over date. Sunny- Stiff W wind. No algae apparent.
Sunny and hazy.  Stiff NE breeze.  Scattered algae globules. Pair of loons with 2 juveniles.
Satellite pass over day (one day late due to weather) . Sunny- NNE wind.
Day late for satellite pass over due to weather. Sunny- clear- calm. Algae bloom.
Satellite pass over day. Partly sunny. Light SE breeze. algae bloom. 2 juvenile loons.
Sunny- SW wind. Satellite pass over date.  Lake level lowest to date.
Satellite pass over date.  Sunny with south wind. High scattered cirrus clouds.

Note: lake level is approx. 5' higher than last fall.  Lake level above AHWM and rising fast.  Wind out of the south.  Mostly sunny.  Heard geese.  Saw solitary loon.  2 main runoff inlets coursing.  Avg for April 2000 10'.

From last measure lake has risen 4". Cloudy- overcast- NE winds. 2 main runoff inlets still flowing.  Goose nesting on southern tip of big island (canadian goose). Note: For lake level measurements used a semi-submerged property stake as a benchmark.

Lake level has stabilized temporarily.  Sunny with scattered clouds.  Wind out of the south.  1 loon- 1 goose (Canadian).  Average secchi depth for May of 2000 was 15.75.  Inlets have stopped flowing.

Lake level dropped 3" since 5/13/01. Both inlets have ceased flowing. Sunny- few clouds- SW winds. 2 loons observed protecting nest (1 egg) from either a pine martin or juvenile fisher. This volunteer and family went swimming for 1st time this season.
Lake level stable from previous reading.  Stiff wind out of the north.  Sunny with a few scattered clouds.  Loon nest looted by fisher.  No eggs remain.  No loons observed.
Sunny- breeze out of the SE.  Lake level up 2" from last reading.  One loon observed on lake.
Sunny- breeze out of the north.  Algae bloom starting off heavily for the season.  Duckweed observed for first time in my four years.  Lake level down 1" from last reading.
Mostly sunny- some clouds.  Breeze out of SE.  Observed a pair of loons.  Lake level appears to have dropped a couple of inches.
Sunny- partly cloudy.  Wind out of the north.  Heavy algae.  1 loon.  Lake water level stable since 7/4/01.
Wind of NE- sunny.  Lake level down 9" from 7/4/01 and 11" down from 4/24/01.
Lake level appears to be at the AHWM.  Lake level down 6" from 8/31/01.  Lake level down 1'-5" from 4/24/01 reading.  Sunny- clear- no breeze.  No wildlife observed.
Lake level from last reading unchanged.  Sunny- stiff breeze out of the south.  High cirrus clouds.  No wildlife observed.
Sunny with high cirrus clouds- North winds at 10-15 mph- lake level is very high (4-6" at property stake benchmark- no wildlife is observed.
Sunny with partial clouds- winds out of the NNE at 10-15 mph- lake level is remaining high- but dropped 6" from last week- turkey vulture observed.
Sunny- clear- variable breeze- lake level up 2" to 4' 2" after heavy rains- no wildlife observed.
Clear- sunny- stiff SE breeze- lake level remains above AHWM at 4' 2" on property stake benchmark- saw 2 loons- swallows and a large tree frog.
This reading follows a day of 4" rainfall- lake level up 2" and rising- high cirrus clouds- sunny- mild NE breeze- 1 loon sighted- firework debris sighted in the water.
No rain for 6 days prior to this reading- sunny and cloudless- SE breeze- lake level currently at 4' 3" on property stake benchmark (down 1")- observed 1 loon and 1 blue heron.
NE breeze- high cirrus clouds- sunny- lake level has dropped 6" since 6/1/2002 and 3" since last week- and observed 1 lone loon.
Sunny with scattered clouds- NW wind- 1 loon observed- water depth at 3' 8" at the property stake- down 4" since 7/23/2002.
SE winds at 25-30 mph- sunny with high cirrus clouds- lake level at 3' 7" at the property stake- down 1"- 2 loons observed- 2 groups of musky fisherman on the lake.
Sunny with scattered clouds- SW winds- lake level is steady with 8/14/2002 reading- 1 loon and 1 bald eagle observed- and 2 boats on the lake fishing.
Sunny with scattered clouds- intermittent breeze out of the NNW- sparse algal bloom evident- lake level steady at 3' 7".
Sunny and clear- SE winds at 10-15 mph- algal bloom evident- lake level up 2" to 3' 9" at property stake benchmark.
South wind 5-10 mph. Sunny and cloudless. Water level 2'7" at property stake benchmark.  Lake level down 1'2" 2002 final of 3'9" of 9/17/02.  Observed 2 loons and 1 bald eagle.
NW breeze 2-5 mph.  Sunny with scattered clouds.  The two inlets were coursing.  Water level 3'2" (up 7" from last week following heavy rains).
Wind 10-15 mph out of north.  Sunny with high cirrus clouds.  Heavy concentrations of wind - driven algae bloom in south bay.  Water level 3'7"- up 5" from last reading and up 12" from 5/3/03.

5-10 mph wind gusts out of the southeast. Sunny and partly cloudy. Very heavy pollen concentration in the lake.  Water level 3'5"- down 2" from last reading.  1 loon.  Note: could not determine algae due to pollen.
Light and variable winds. Sunny with high cirrus clouds. Pollen concentration greatly dimished.  Water level 3'- 4.5".  2 loons.  Note: hard to distinguish algae presence.
5-10 mph winds.  Sunny with scattered clouds.  Some particles in water (algae).  Water level 3' 3".  1 loon observed.
5-10 mph winds- variable direction.  Sunny with scattered clouds.  Algae bloom present - moderate.  Water level 3' 7" at property stake.  Lake level up 4" from 5 days of rain.  2 loons sighted.
Sunny- partly cloudy. Wind 5mph out of SE.  Heavy algae bloom present.  Water level 3' 2".  Litter debris and fireworks debris collected in south bay.
Sunny with high cumulus clouds.  Wind out of southwest at 10 mph.  Heavy algae bloom.  Water is "pea soup" green.  Fireworks debris in water.  Water level is 3' 2".

Sunny with scattered clouds throughout.  Wind out of SW 5 mph.  Heavy algae bloom present.  Water level 2'11" at property stake (down 3" from previous).  This reading coordinated with the Kent State University Secchi Dip-In.
Very green- though no visble scum on the surface.

column1: This test was done in cooperation with the Deep Lake Volunteers

column2: Sunny with sparse- scattered clouds.  Wind 5-10 mph out of SW.  2 loons sighted.  Heavy algae bloom continues with large concentration at surface.  Water level at 2'-7" on property stake.  Lake water level now at 5/3/03 reading.
Sunny with sparse scattered clouds.  Wind 5-10 mph out of SW.  2 loons sited.  Heavy algae bloom continues with large concentration at surface.  Water height at 2'-6"
Wind 10-15 mph out of North.  Sunny- scattered clouds.  Heavy algae continues.  Water level 2'5" at property stake.  Lake level down 1" from previous reading.
Wind 5-10 mph out of SW.  Sunny with scattered clouds.  Algae bloom remains dense.  Lake level 2'-2" at property stake.  Lake level down 3" from previous level.
no bluegreen today- 2 loons out- no babies. Bottom temp 43.1 F.
Sunny- partially cloudy.  Algae less concentrated.  Lake bed at shoreline covered with green coating.  Lake level at property stake 2'-0".  Lake level down 2".

Sunny- variable winds 5-10 mph.  Algae continues to be less concentrated.  Lake bottom "coated".  Lake level at property stake is 1'=7".  Down 5" from last reading.  Lake level 1' lower than first reading of the season.
Sunny and Hazy- no wind.  Algae slicks observed in south bay.  Sparse algae globuals suspended in water.  Lake level remains at 1'-7" on property stake.
Sunny and windy. 10-15 mph wind. No signs of algae apparent.  Lake level has fallen 7" from last reading.  Lake level at 1' 0" on property stake.
Lake full of leaves- 1 bald eagle. Bottom temp 44.9 F.  Dave

column1: Blumer left new grant equipment with the group.

column2: Cloudy- windy- sparse snowflakes- saw two loons- cold 47 F.  Ice off lake 4/15/2004.
Cloudy- windy- one blue heron.  Air 76.4 F.
Partly cloudy- windy.  One loon.  Air 78 F.
Windy.  One loon.  Beautiful sunny day. Air 66.2 F.
Two bald eagles- 2 loons.  Nice day.  Some clouds.  Air 50 F.
sunny day + light winds- spotted a bald eagle and loons

column1: Water level well below ordinary water high water mark

Bill and Bruce used both water level and transit to show water level = 85.78 feet (relative to monument = 90.4 ft)
